account_id.Description: Configure API client to always use that account

api_base_path.Description: Configure the base path used by the API client

api_client_logging.Description: Whether to print logs from the API client (using the default log library logger)

api_hostname.Description: Configure the hostname used by the API client

api_user_service_key.Description: A special Cloudflare API key good for a restricted set of endpoints

max_backoff.Description: Maximum backoff period in seconds after failed API calls

min_backoff.Description: Minimum backoff period in seconds after failed API calls

retries.Description: Maximum number of retries to perform when an API request fails

rps.Description: RPS limit to apply when making calls to the API

compliance_status.Description: The workspace one device compliance status.

domain.Description: The domain that the client must join.

enabled.Description: True if the firewall must be enabled.

exists.Description: Checks if the file should exist.

require_all.Description: True if all drives must be encrypted.

running.Description: Checks if the application should be running

sha256.Description: The sha256 hash of the file.

thumbprint.Description: The thumbprint of the file certificate.

description.Description: A description of the fallback domain, displayed in the client UI.

dns_server.Description: A list of IP addresses to handle domain resolution.

suffix.Description: The domain suffix to match when resolving locally.

mode.Description: The mode of the split tunnel policy. Either 'include' or 'exclude'.

host.Description: The domain name for the tunnel.
